5000|$|The copper-chlorine cycle (Cu-Cl cycle) is a four-step <b>thermochemical</b> <b>cycle</b> for the {{production}} of hydrogen. The Cu-Cl cycle is a hybrid process that employs both thermochemical and electrolysis steps.It has a maximum temperature requirement of about 530 degrees Celsius.|$|E
