50|$|The hybrid {{sulfur cycle}} (HyS) is a two-step water-splitting process {{intended}} {{to be used for}} hydrogen production. Based on sulfur oxidation and reduction, it is classified as a hybrid <b>thermochemical</b> <b>cycle</b> because it uses an electrochemical (instead of a thermochemical) reaction for one of the two steps. The remaining thermochemical step is shared with the sulfur-iodine cycle.|$|E
